subSubSection.paragraph:
Distylodon sonkeanum

is endemic to the coastal part of the Lower Guinea Domain (
White 1979
) of the Guineo-Congolian Region. It is known from a single locality in South Region of Cameroon (
Fig. 3
). The only population known so far was found in the lowland evergreen forest at 100 m elevation, growing epiphytically on a fallen branch.
